18/11/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Former President Rexhep Meidani announced Monday (17 November) his withdrawal from the race to become Socialist Party leader. His decision came after former Prime Minister Ilir Meta said he supports both Meidani and Tirana Mayor Edi Rama for the post. Meidani said that he wants to remain neutral and avoid conflict. Prime Minister Fatos Nano is now Rama's only rival for the job. (Albanian Daily News, ATA - 17/11/03)
